// Notes: ['Use when modeling Feistel-family ciphers such as DES-like designs.', 'Switch to concatenation form `r # (...)` if the surrounding code expects a flat block instead of `[2]HALF_TYPE`.', 'Usually paired with a final half-swap before the final permutation.']
round : (ROUND_KEY_TYPE, [2]HALF_TYPE) -> [2]HALF_TYPE
