// [Template] Convert 1-based specification indices to 0-based Cryptol indices
// Notes: ['Very common when porting textbook or standards permutation tables into Cryptol.', 'Use the normalized table only for Cryptol indexing operators like `@`, `@@`, `!`, or `!!`.', 'Keep the original table as a separate artifact if traceability back to the standard matters.']
zeroBasify xs = [ i - 1 | i <- xs ]

NORMALIZED_NAME = zeroBasify TABLE_NAME

